service.name: Newstart Allowance
service.description: Newstart Allowance (NSA) is designed to ensure that people aged 22 and over who are unemployed receive an adequate level of income & participate in activities designed to increase their chances of finding work. NSA can be paid to temporarily incapacitated people who do not qualify for Sickness Allowance (SkA) because they are under the statutory age limit for SkA or because they do not have a job or study to return to.
